Digital Locker System 🔐

A Java-based Digital Locker System built using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles.
The project allows users to securely store, access, and manage digital documents/files in a locker-like environment.

👉 This project was developed as part of learning Java and OOP concepts.

---

🚀 Features

* User authentication (login system)
* Store and retrieve digital files securely
* Organized folder/locker structure
* Simple console-based interface for easy navigation
* Implements OOP concepts (Encapsulation, Inheritance, Polymorphism, Abstraction)

---
 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Java (JDK 8+) – Core programming
* OOP Principles– Project structure and design
* File Handling – Storing and retrieving documents(consider file as a string)

---

📂 Project Setup

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/Jeya-Surya/Digital-Locker-System.git
2. Open the project in any IDE (IntelliJ, Eclipse, VS Code).
3. Compile and run the `Main.java` file.

---

🔮 Future Enhancements

